The '''''Texas Journal of Science''''' is a [[peer reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering all areas of basic and applied sciences, as well as [[science education]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.speciation.net/Database/Journals/Texas-Journal-of-Science-;i1639 |title=Texas Journal of Science |work=European Virtual Institute for Speciation Analysis |publisher=}}</ref> It is published by the [[Texas Academy of Science]]. The journal is abstracted and indexed in [[BIOSIS Previews]] and [[The Zoological Record]]<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref> and was in previous years also covered by [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2016-05-29}}</ref> It obtained its last [[impact factor]] of 0.113 in 2010, but its listing in the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'' has since been discontinued.

